metadata.name: Chop Chop #8
metadata.description:
Chop Chop is a complementary collection to Caterpillars that I prepared to thank my collectors for the amazing love and interest you showed to my work. I did not want to force my way to your wallets with unsolicited thank-you nfts, so all holders of Caterpillars will have a reserve spot to mint at least 1 tokens per wallet for 0 tez ( I dont understand the reserve options fully, sorry - 128 editions reserved for holders of Caterpillars) . 

The holders of this collection will have reserve spots for my next  collection. The reserve spots will be held for one week from minting, and I prefer the unreserved editions to be fair game for anyone, so first come, first served.

I decided to re-work this older project of mine because it was going to take some time for me to prepare an independent and novel collection and also wanted to continue learning new things. The concept is Paul Klee meets Vector Math and Flow Fields, as you can see the visuals are heavily inspired by Paul Klee's work :)

Under the hood, the circles and triangles act as repulsive forces that break and distort the grid, and push the squares in their range out of their way, forming some holes in the fabric created by the same algo that made Caterpillars. 

I have only added one rarity feature which is the palette because this one uses almost all the palettes from Caterpillars (minus neon dreams). I am hoping that this project will not be about rarity, but more like a thank-you gift and an easy way to access my future work.

Well, I hope you will like it...

- Press "s" to save a png.

- Also, 33% royalty split wth the Processing Foundation, % 33 with the minters (if there will be any secondary sales) 

DISCLAIMER :
I am very very new to coding and not very good at this. I have tried to clean up the code as best as I could, and I hope that there is nothing terribly wrong left inside.

metadata.name: Antiflow #28
metadata.description:
"Opposites are not contradictory but complementary." -Â Niels Bohr

The concept of yin and yang is an ancient philosophy aboutÂ how opposingÂ forces are not only complementary but actually give rise to each other. This ideaÂ reverberates through nature, art, and life itself. Now it is at the heart of modern physics. Perhaps this is a fundamentalÂ law of nature baked into theÂ very fabric of existence.

Antiflow is an exploration of how balanced complexity can ariseÂ from chaos by harnessing the dynamic interplay of opposingÂ forces. To that end we were inspired to create this wildly uniqueÂ set by mixing modern physics concepts with abstract expressionism and retro 3D primitives.

The aspect ratioÂ is 3:2 to facilitate poster size prints and device wallpapers. Results are presented without borders, noise, or other effects to allow for maximum detail. Feel free to rotate in whatever direction you choose for the best display.

Press "S" to save at a higher definition.

metadata.name: Chaos Machine Part 1 #10
metadata.description:
This work of generative art explores the transitional and interactive spaces between determinism and randomness, between chaos and order, between human and computer, between surface and essence, and between artist and audience. 

Enjoy the art at the aesthetic level as it is generated by algorithm and chance, but also look deeper, explore, and see what u might discover.

Secondary royalties from this piece will be split with the original minter, and ownership of this piece will inform the access list for future related works.

metadata.name: Sherwood #299
metadata.description:
In the forest, foggy, cloudy weather creates a mysterious, otherworldly atmosphere.

----

Controls:
s or [double click] - save
1 through 8 - set the pixel density for higher resolutions. Base is 2000x1000.
d - increase debug level (none, overlay, overlay + animated drawing)
D - decrease debug level
[plus] or [equal] - increase the edition of the mint (see a new location with the same features)
[minus] - decrease the edition, to a minimum of zero

Made with:
- p5js
- Simplex noise (hills, cleared/forested, grass height, tree size & separation)
- Poisson disk sampling (tree distribution)
